✅ Explanation:
● Unary — modifies single value (++/-- before or after).
● Arithmetic — math operators: + - * / %.
● Shift — shifts bits left/right << >>.
● Relational — compare two values (>, <, ==, !=).
● Bitwise — operates on bits (& | ^ ~).
● Logical — works on conditions (&& || !).
● Ternary — short if-else: condition ? true : false.
● Assignment — =, +=, -=, *=, /= etc.
